<div id="B 380"><br />An overview of international business designed to provide a global perspective on international trade and direct investment. Reviews international cultural, political, legal, and economic environments and their effect on marketing, production, and human resource management strategy.</div>
<div><br /><br /><a onclick="switchMenu('COMM 350');" style="text-decoration: none;" target="_self">COMM&nbsp;350 - Group Dynamics</a><br />3 credits<br />
<div id="COMM 350"><br />Analysis of theory and practice of human communication in a small group setting, focusing on leadership, participation and evaluation, with emphasis in group norms, roles, cohesion, and conflict.</div>
<br /><br /><a onclick="switchMenu('COMM 397');" style="text-decoration: none;" target="_self">COMM&nbsp;397 - Teamwork and Travel</a><br />1 credit<br />
<div id="COMM 397"><br />Specialized, department-sponsored practicum gives students experience in communication by applying lessons/knowledge learned in class to real-life projects.</div>
<br /><br /><a onclick="switchMenu('COMM 490');" style="text-decoration: none;" target="_self">COMM 490 - Directed Studies/Projects</a><br />1-2 credits<br />
<div id="COMM 490"><br />Individual major projects or research.</div>
<br /><br /><a onclick="switchMenu('ECON 358');" style="text-decoration: none;" target="_self">ECON 358 - International Economics</a><br />3 credits<br />Prerequisites: ECON 150, 151</div>
<div id="ECON 358"><br />An introduction to international trade and finance. It examines international institutions, policies, and issues.</div>
<p><br /><br /><a onclick="switchMenu('ECON 390R');" style="text-decoration: none;" target="_self">ECON 390R - Special Topics</a><br />1-3 credits<br />Prerequisites: ECON 150, 151</p>
<div id="ECON 390R"><br />This arranged course allows students to undertake a special project or further research in the field of economics. Economic Education students study teaching methodologies and prepare course material for teaching economics.div&gt;
<div><br /><br /><a onclick="switchMenu('FDREL 190');" style="text-decoration: none;" target="_self">FDREL 190 - Special Topics in Scripture (Required)</a><br />2 credits<br />
<div id="FDREL 190"><br />For BYU-Idaho students facing special credit situations and for BYU-Idaho travel study students, taught in the term of the travel study, with topics selected which will focus on history, scripture, and culture of the lands visited.</div>
